Function Reference/get media items « WordPress Codex
-----------

Retrieve HTML for media items of post gallery.

The HTML markup retrieved will be created for the progress of SWF Upload
component. Will also create link for showing and hiding the form to
modify the image attachment.

Usage
-----

` <?php get_media_items( $post_id, $errors ); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$post_id` 
:   ([*int*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Int "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Optional. Post ID.
    Default: *None*

 `$errors` 
:   ([*array*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Array "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Errors for attachment, if any.
    Default: *None*

Return Values
-------------

 `` `(string)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   

Change Log
----------

Since: [2.5](/Version_2.5 "Version 2.5")

Source File
-----------

`get_media_items()` is located in `wp-admin/includes/media.php`

